title: Bird strike after takeoff sends United Airlines flight back to Chicago
description: A bird strike shortly after takeoff sent a United Airlines flight back to Chicago's O'Hare International Airport on Friday, the airline said.

title: See moment SpaceX crew splashes down
description: Four astronauts boarded a SpaceX Crew Dragon capsule and returned home from the International Space Station, bringing an end to their nearly six-month stay aboard the orbiting laboratory.

title: Late night hosts question if Trump would comply with Jan. 6 subpoena
description: Late night hosts cracked a few jokes after the House January 6 Committee voted unanimously to subpoena former president Donald Trump for testimony and documents.

title: 'Rape has become a weapon' for Haiti gangs, says UN
description: As Haiti reels from a cascade of crises, the United Nations has released a grim report accusing the country's powerful gangs of using rape as a tool of intimidation and control.

title: Trump operative seen on video in Georgia voting system breach testifies before special grand jury
description: A pro-Trump operative who was caught on tape participating in a Georgia voting system breach after the 2020 election has testified before the special grand jury investigating efforts to overturn the outcome in that state, two sources familiar with the matter tell CNN.

title: Robbie Coltrane, Hagrid in 'Harry Potter' films, dead at 72
description: Robbie Coltrane, the actor who brought to life the lovable gamekeeper Hagrid in the Harry Potter film franchise, died on Friday, according to his agent, Scott Henderson. He was 72.

title: Humans can dive deeper into the world's oceans than ever before with Alvin
description: Black smoke appears to rise from chimney-like formations of the hottest and deepest known hydrothermal vents on Earth.

description: Heavy floods have caused thousands to evacuate in the Australian southeast states of Victoria, New South Wales and Tasmania.

title: What King Charles III's coronation might look like
description: Mark your calendars, royal-watchers. King Charles III will be crowned in Westminster Abbey on May 6, 2023, eight months after he succeeded his mother.

title: A UK TV station bought a painting by Hitler. A studio audience will vote on whether to destroy it
description: British broadcaster Channel 4 has received stinging criticism over plans for a new show that will allow a studio audience to decide whether to destroy a painting by Adolf Hitler.

title: Sanctions hurt Russia's ability to replenish military supplies: intel
description: Western sanctions have sharply curtailed Russia's ability to replenish the munitions it is using in Ukraine, according to a new analysis from the Office of the Director of National Intelligence, forcing Moscow to task its intelligence services with finding ways to evade restrictions and procure the critical technology and parts to sustain its war effort.

title: As the US-Saudi oil spat intensifies, what are Biden's options?
description: The Saudi-American relationship appears to have hit rock bottom.

title: A dad's advice to neighborhood kids: Don't use gay as an insult
description: Imparting life lessons to your own kids is part and parcel of parenting, but what about doing that for other people's kids? When (if ever) is it appropriate to step in to issue a value judgment and draw a hard line in the sand when it involves not just your child but other children as well?

title: Trump issues lengthy response to January 6 hearing
description: Former President Donald Trump does not say whether he will comply with the subpoena by the House select committee investigating the January 6 Capitol Hill insurrection, in a lengthy response to the committee posted on Truth Social. CNN's John Avlon and columnist Scott Jennings discuss.

title: Putin: No need for more 'massive' strikes in Ukraine 'for now'
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin said Friday he had "no regrets" over his deadly missile attacks on civilian targets across Ukraine earlier this week, but said there was no need for more "massive" strikes for now.

title: The biography of bling

description: Tapping into the twin markets of A) lovers of rom-coms and B) recovering English majors, "Rosaline" promotes a fleetingly mentioned "Romeo and Juliet" character front and center, then builds a very clever and breezy movie around her. The result is a welcome starring showcase for Kaitlyn Dever more likely to prosper in the hamlet of Hulu than it would have fared in the province of theaters.

title: I first knew her as a teapot, but she spent seven decades redefining what a woman could be
description: Her story began like a classic Hollywood fairytale, but that's not how it ended. Angela Lansbury, who died on Tuesday aged 96, starred in her first film, "Gaslight," in 1944 at just 19 years old. She'd been signed by MGM Studios just two years previously, having studied acting in New York City after her family, which had fallen on hard times, was forced to flee their home in Blitz-stricken London.

title: Look of the Week: Taylor Russell's dramatic red carpet corset
description: At last weekend's premiere of Italian director Luca Guadagnino's new film "Bones and All" during London's BFI Film Festival, actor Taylor Russell cemented herself as one to watch on the red carpet wearing a striking head-to-toe Schiaparelli look and boned corset.

title: Beyond Meat executive who allegedly bit a man's nose will leave the company

title: One of Turkey's most spectacular hiking destinations
description: A rich palette of shimmering caramel swirls, ochers, creams and pinks unfolds across the landscape like an enormous handwoven carpet. Stands of poplars line paths carved by ancient lava flows from three now extinct volcanoes, crisscrossing valleys studded with conical peribacı.
